{
  "texts": [
    "In 2019, an estimated 970 million individuals worldwide suffered from mental illness, accounting for 12.5% of the global population 2.",
    "Anxiety and depression are among the most prevalent psychological conditions, affecting 301 million and 280 million individuals respectively 2.",
    "However, they often go undetected or untreated, and the resources allocated to the diagnosis and treatment of mental illness are far less than the negative impact it has on society 3.",
    "Focusing specifically on the UK, the scale of the mental health crisis is significant.",
    "Figures show that one in six individuals in England reported experiencing a common mental health problem in a given week 4."
  ]
}